Round 1:
[Patient] "What exercises do you recommend for me?"
[Educator] "Walking or swimming are good options for your heart health."

Round 2:
[Patient] "Is it safe for me to do weightlifting?"
[Educator] "Start with light weights and gradually increase to avoid straining your heart."

Round 3:
[Patient] "Can I do high-intensity workouts?"
[Educator] "It's best to stick to moderate intensity exercises to protect your heart."

Round 4:
[Patient] "Should I do cardio or strength training?"
[Educator] "A combination of both cardio and strength training can be beneficial for your heart."

Round 5:
[Patient] "Are there any exercises I should avoid?"
[Educator] "Avoid heavy lifting or exercises that strain your heart too much."

Round 6:
[Patient] "How often should I exercise?"
[Educator] "Try to aim for at least 30 minutes of exercise most days of the week."

Round 7:
[Patient] "Can I exercise if I feel tired?"
[Educator] "Listen to your body and rest if you feel too tired to exercise."

Round 8:
[Patient] "Can I exercise outside in my neighborhood?"
[Educator] "Yes, walking or jogging in your safe neighborhood can be a great way to exercise."

Round 9:
[Patient] "Should I do yoga or Pilates for my heart?"
[Educator] "Yoga can be beneficial for relaxation, but it's important to also include cardio exercises."

Round 10:
[Patient] "What if I have joint pain while exercising?"
[Educator] "Consider low-impact exercises like swimming or biking to reduce joint pain."